## Terms of Appointment of Independent Directors

The Independent Directors are appointed for a term of five years, subject to re-appointment in accordance with the provisions of the Companies Act, 2013 and the SEBI (Listing Obligations and Disclosure Requirements) Regulations, 2015. They do not receive any performance-linked incentives. They receive sitting fees for attending Board and Committee meetings as determined by the Board.

## Terms of Appointment of Non-Executive Director

B.M. Vyas, the Non-Executive Director, is appointed for a term liable to retire by rotation. He receives sitting fees for attending Board and Committee meetings as determined by the Board.

## Terms of Appointment of Additional and Nominee Director

Ramesh Chandak, the Additional and Nominee Director, is appointed up to the ensuing Annual General Meeting. He receives sitting fees for attending Board and Committee meetings as determined by the Board.

